                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client with cancer of the prostate who has undergone a prostatectomy. Which action would the nurse plan to include in discharge instructions?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe client who has undergone a prostatectomy needs to avoid lifting objects heavier than 20 lb (9 kg) for at least 6 weeks. Driving a car and sitting for long periods are restricted for at least 3 weeks. A high daily fluid intake would be maintained to limit clot formation and prevent infection. Small pieces of tissue or blood clots may be passed during urination for up to 2 weeks after surgery; this is an expected occurrence.",
                        "id": "49e8c05481db49878dd4caf294f468cc",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1c8c5029847c4cf68ba584997287744a",
                                "content": "Concern about the outcome of surgery"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "24e36d222eaa4795b7208ab94b7876fc",
                                "content": "Continuous pain because of the effects of cancer"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d33b34b1e0b44cccb3e4ec0468ce55b0",
                                "content": "Appearance disturbance as a result of the presence of a suprapubic catheter"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d23dad78fc4e4ad991865ddd61f59352",
                                "content": "Concern about caring for self at home because of insufficient help after discharge"
                            }
                        ],
