                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client is admitted to the nursing unit after undergoing radical prostatectomy for cancer. The nurse anticipates that which problem would be of most concern to the client in the immediate postoperative period?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIn the immediate postoperative period, the client who has had surgery for cancer may experience fear or concern related to the uncertain outcome of surgery. Postoperative pain is classified as acute, not continuous. The client may experience an alteration in appearance, but this is more likely to be related to the anticipated change in sexual function than the presence of the suprapubic catheter. The priority focus in the immediate postoperative period is not on concerns that apply to hospital discharge.",
                        "id": "825529f4746c421d91a9ac39c9d62097",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "291f667d21bb455ca3d553e8fd708fe3",
                                "content": "Elevating the limb"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a2a6e915c6a14703aa4ae4c7763d40ca",
                                "content": "Monitoring vital signs every 4 hours"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "607a78e9cd814807b9ceef826808ff61",
                                "content": "Administering opioid analgesics intramuscularly"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "eb2ebdc03a1f4bd085b933f4db503f80",
                                "content": "Monitoring the biopsy site for swelling, bleeding, or hematoma"
                            }
                        ],
